aracteristic forenames:  Jewish Avrohom, Bronya, Eliezer, Naftali.","Jewish (Ashkenazic): habitational name for someone from Apt (see   Apt  ).","English: habitational name from Aptor in Marldon, Devon, composed of Old English <i>uppe</i> ‘up, above’ + <i>torr</i> ‘rocky outcrop’."]}]},{"name":"Jevan","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["French (Nord):","metonymic occupational name for a basket maker, from <i>van</i> ‘the winnowing basket’, with fused masculine definite article <i>le</i>.","habitational name from Le Van, a place in Somme."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Jenkin","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Transferred use of the surname, which is derived from the medieval given name <i>Jankin</i>. This was a pet form of the boy's name   Jan  , with the diminutive suffix <i>-kin</i>. The modern given name is popular in Wales, where the surnames <i>Jenkin</i> and <i>Jenkins</i> are common."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Jenkin ap Jevan was born about 1397, in Wales, his father, Jevan Ap Howel, was 42 and his mother, Mrs Jevan ap Howel, was 34. He had at least 1 son with ferch Morgan."},"et":{"ABT 1397–":"umbes 1397–Surnud","1397–Male":"1397–Surnud","1401–Female":"1401–Surnud","1440–Male":"1440–Surnud","1357–Male":"1357–Surnud","1365–Female":"1365–Surnud","1357":"1357","1401":"1401","ABT 1397":"umbes 1397","1365":"1365","1397":"1397","1440":"1440","abt 1440":"umbes 1440","Wales":"Wales","of Trecastle, Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales"},"fi":{"ABT 1397–":"noin 1397–Kuollut","1397–Male":"1397–Kuollut","1401–Female":"1401–Kuollut","1440–Male":"1440–Kuollut","1357–Male":"1357–Kuollut","1365–Female":"1365–Kuollut","1357":"1357","1401":"1401","ABT 1397":"noin 1397","1365":"1365","1397":"1397","1440":"1440","abt 1440":"noin 1440","Wales":"Wales","of Trecastle, Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales"},"fr":{"ABT 139